{
  "_source": "residentevil123 forum 't3242' (item ID table)",
  "_note": "IDs verified from forum; item-record opcode is 0x62 (22 bytes). Key items gate progression.",
  "_lock": "The 'allItems' table is the id->name->category source of truth, locked to DinoCrisis1 by ItemTableTests: every DinoCrisis1.ItemPool entry's id/name/category must match a row here, and every category=='key' id must be in DinoCrisis1.KeyItemIds. The 'pool' weights/membership below are an informational reference only — the code's ItemPool is hand-tuned and intentionally differs. Edit allItems + the code together, or the test fails.",
  "_weaponAmmo_note": "Weapon-id -> compatible ammo-ids, the linked-ammo source of truth (ITEM-RANDO-PLAN.md §2). Mirrored by DinoCrisis1.AmmoForWeapon and locked by ItemTableTests. Confidence: handgun/shotgun high; grenade-gun round-sharing medium (mis-weights ammo only, never beatability). startingWeapons = weapons Regina begins with, so their ammo is always linked.",
  "_weaponPartUpgrades_note": "Weapon-PART id -> the weapon it upgrades into, so a placed part links the upgraded weapon's ammo (ITEM-RANDO-PLAN.md §6/§7.3). Only Handgun Slides (0x0e -> Glock 35 0x07) is mapped: it is the one part whose upgrade introduces NEW ammo (40S&W 0x17) and whose base (Glock 34) is the always-present starting weapon. The shotgun parts reuse shotgun ammo (already linked via the Shotgun pickup), so mapping them would only risk linking shotgun ammo off a stray stock with no shotgun.",
  "_weaponPartBase_note": "Weapon-PART id -> the BASE weapon it requires to be useful (ITEM-RANDO-PLAN.md §7.3). Drives the weapon-upgrade-chance feature: an upgrade part is only placed when its base weapon is in the seed, and then only with probability RandomizerConfig.WeaponUpgradeChance. 0x0b/0x0c (shotgun parts/stock) need a Shotgun 0x01; 0x0d/0x0e (handgun sights/slides) need the Handgun 0x05 (the start weapon, always present); 0x0f (grenade-gun part) needs the Grenade Gun 0x09. Mirrored by DinoCrisis1.WeaponForPart, locked by ItemTableTests.",
  "startingWeapons": ["0x05"],
  "weaponPartUpgrades": { "0x0e": "0x07" },
  "weaponPartBase": { "0x0b": "0x01", "0x0c": "0x01", "0x0d": "0x05", "0x0e": "0x05", "0x0f": "0x09" },
  "_weaponUpgradeVariants_note": "Base weapon -> { part-id: resulting upgraded-weapon variant }, for the EXPERIMENTAL pre-upgraded-weapon feature (ITEM-RANDO-PLAN.md §7.3): with RandomizerConfig.PreUpgradedWeaponChance (default 0, OFF), a found base weapon is placed already-upgraded (the variant id) instead of base + a loose part. These variant ids (0x02-0x08, 0x0a) are NEVER vanilla world pickups in DC1 (the game only places base 0x01/0x09 and combines parts at runtime), so a direct variant pickup is UNVALIDATED and the feature is default-off pending CE/playtest. Confidence: shotgun/handgun combinations high; grenade 0x09+0x0f->0x0a medium. Mirrored by DinoCrisis1.WeaponUpgradeVariants, locked by ItemTableTests.",
  "weaponUpgradeVariants": {
    "0x01": { "0x0b": "0x02", "0x0c": "0x03" },
    "0x02": { "0x0c": "0x04" },
