  "_weaponFamilies_note": "Player-facing weapon FAMILY -> { name, ids }, the source of truth for the per-family EnabledWeapons toggles (ITEM-RANDO-PLAN.md §7.4). Each family groups a base weapon, its custom variants, and its upgrade parts; every weapon/weapon_part id (0x01-0x0f) appears in exactly one family. Mirrored by DinoCrisis1.WeaponFamilyOf / WeaponFamilies and locked by ItemTableTests. Disabling a family (RandomizerConfig.EnabledWeaponFamilies) drops its ids from pool placement; the order here is the UI/CLI display order. The Handgun is Regina's start weapon, so disabling it only removes handgun pickups/upgrades — the starting Glock 34 (and its 9mm) is unaffected.",
